📌 Problem (simple words)

Given a string, find the first character that appears only once.

👉 Return its index
👉 If none exists → return -1

✅ Example
s = "leetcode"
l → 1 time ✅
e → 3 times ❌
t → 1 time

👉 First unique = 'l' → index 0

Solution 1: with hashmap

class Solution {
    fun firstUniqChar(s: String): Int {
         val map = mutableMapOf<Char,Int>()
  
        for(i in s.indices){
            // store frequency
           map[s[i]] = map.getOrDefault(s[i],0) + 1 
         }
  
        for(i in s.indices){
            // get first item whose frequency was 1
             if(map[s[i]] == 1) {    
            return i
            }
        }
        return -1
    }
}
